										</div>
										<div class="col-12 col-md-8">
											<p>Templates are pre-formatted documents or files that increase the speed, quality & consistency of business document creation. They can be for manual use (people manually entering data) or automated (databases or other systems automatically inserting data). Good templates only require the bare essential data to be entered, usually follow pertinent standards, and minimise duplicate entry requirements. Some templates deploy macros or scripts to automate some data entry or processing that a user might typically have to do manually.</p>  
											<p>Tom has experience designing & programming a wide range of templates including drawing borders, calculators / standard calculations, pro-forma reports, quotes, invoices & purchase orders, data entry forms, data collection forms, automated spreadsheets & much more...</p>
